body:
In https://github.com/llvm/circt/pull/8405, I introduced changes where an operand captured from outside a layer block will cause the operand to be replaced with an XMR to _a node_ driven by the operand's value with a prefix of `_layer_probe`.

This is sub-optimal as it leaves dead code in the design. However, it was empirically necessary to allow for heavier optimization of circuits. E.g., the following circuit is a reduction of circuit that proved problematic:

``` mlir
firrtl.circuit "Foo" {
  firrtl.layer @A bind {}
  firrtl.module @Foo(
    in %clk: !firrtl.clock,
    in %a: !firrtl.uint<1>,
    in %b: !firrtl.uint<8>,
    out %c: !firrtl.uint<8>
  ) {
    %c1_ui1 = firrtl.constant 1 : !firrtl.uint<1>
    %reg = firrtl.reg %clk : !firrtl.clock, !firrtl.uint<8>
    %x = firrtl.wire : !firrtl.uint<1>
    %0 = firrtl.or %a, %x : (!firrtl.uint<1>, !firrtl.uint<1>) -> !firrtl.uint<1>
    %1 = firrtl.mux(%0, %b, %reg) : (!firrtl.uint<1>, !firrtl.uint<8>, !firrtl.uint<8>) -> !firrtl.uint<8>
    %2 = firrtl.not %a : (!firrtl.uint<1>) -> !firrtl.uint<1>
    firrtl.matchingconnect %x, %2 : !firrtl.uint<1>
    firrtl.matchingconnect %reg, %1 : !firrtl.uint<8>
    firrtl.matchingconnect %c, %reg : !firrtl.uint<8>
    firrtl.layerblock @A {
      firrtl.assert %clk, %x, %c1_ui1, "" : !firrtl.clock, !firrtl.uint<1>, !firrtl.uint<1>
    }
  }
}
```

Without this dead node, I would get Verilog that looked like:

```verilog
 reg  [7:0] reg_0;
  wire       x = ~a;
  always @(posedge clk) begin
    if (a | x)
      reg_0 <= b;
```

The `if` condition is `a | ~a`. However, introducing a symbol on the wire `%x` will block later optimizations.

Figure out a way to untangle this and remove the `_layer_probe` nodes. This may be able to be handled with improved optimizations in the FIRRTL pipeline.
